        <ReportItem id="q1" type="Radio" blobItem="Q1" blobType="BLOB_TEXT" options="True|False">
            <![CDATA[
                <h3>Social isolation is defined as physical isolation from others.</h3>
                {$item}
            ]]>
        </ReportItem>
    </ReportSection>
    
    <!-- Answer 1 -->
    <ReportSection id="a1" tooltip="Answers1" name="Answer1" title="QUESTION 1" blobSection="QUIZ" type="QuizReportSection" hidden="true">
        <ReportItem id="q1" type="Answer" blobItem="Q1" blobType="BLOB_TEXT" label="Answer 1" answer="False">
            <![CDATA[
                {$item}
                <b>The truth is, social isolation isn’t just about being physically alone.</b>
                <p>
                    While social isolation can include physical isolation, it’s much more than that. Social isolation is subjective, meaning we all experience it differently. Some people may feel lonely even when they are around other people. Some people may be alone and not feel lonely, in fact, they may prefer it.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Social isolation can be both physical and emotional.
                </p>
            ]]>
        </ReportItem>
    </ReportSection>
    
    <!-- Question 2 -->
    <ReportSection id="q2" tooltip="Quiz" name="Quiz2" title="QUESTION 2" blobSection="QUIZ" type="QuizReportSection" hidden="true">
        <ReportItem id="q2" type="Radio" blobItem="Q2" blobType="BLOB_TEXT" options="True|False">
            <![CDATA[
                <h3>Every human being has the same social needs.</h3>
                {$item}
            ]]>
        </ReportItem>
    </ReportSection>
    
    <!-- Answer 2 -->
    <ReportSection id="a2" tooltip="Answers1" name="Answer2" title="QUESTION 2" blobSection="QUIZ" type="QuizReportSection" hidden="true">
        <ReportItem id="q2" type="Answer" blobItem="Q2" blobType="BLOB_TEXT" label="Answer 2" answer="False">
            <![CDATA[
                {$item}
                <b>The truth is, we all have different social needs.</b>
                <p>
                    All humans have social needs, but we each have different needs. Social interaction needs can be thought of as a continuum: some people are energized by being with others while some people prefer to be on their own. Most people’s social needs fall somewhere in the middle.
                </p>
                <p>We each have to determine the level of social engagement that is right for us. It’s important to be aware of what your own needs are, because knowing this can help you take steps to find the right amount of social interaction.</p>
            ]]>
        </ReportItem>
    </ReportSection>
    
