            <![CDATA[
                {$item}
                <p>
                    Social interaction has both physical and mental benefits for healthy aging. In addition to the above benefits, being socially active can help improve your mood, contribute to a sense of purpose, can help reduce your risk of Alzheimer’s Disease, and even reduce your risk of malnutrition.
                </p>
                <p>
                    These benefits demonstrate just how important interaction is to healthy aging and to avoiding frailty.
                </p>
